The paper proposes a decentralized algorithm for training deep neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The algorithm is designed to handle communication delays and overlaps computation and communication, which suggests a focus on distributed systems (cs.DC) and distributed algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also mentions achieving state-of-the-art results, indicating a focus on improving the performance of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the use of synchronous updates suggests a focus on control and optimization (cs.SY).
